column5: Hi there  Somebody had told me that if i sent my mercury highfive ss prop back to them, they will fix the nicks and blueprint it for a very very low price.........IS this true, has anybody done it before?? Apparently it only costs $150 and comes back looking brand new  Anybody know if this is true? If so, where exactly do I send it/how long does it take?  thanks!

There is a fellow in Hagersville that rebuilds props for a reasonable cost, J & J MARINE SERVICES Prop Shop Est. 1988 P.O. Box 731 Hagersville, Ont. N0A 1H0 905.768.9188 I have dealt with him before and he seems to be OK. He re-did my Johnson 20hp prop for $50.00
Your right homefries, this guy is a terrific person.
i had him do a prop of mine and it took 2 months, rather then the 1 week they told me...  not impressed  he did good work though!!
what no grinder marks on your blades, prob changed your pitch a few degrees ,oh well maybe he perfected the craft,dont mess with that high 5 send it to someone that knows there poop esp with SS

City Wide Welding Inc 1867 Drew Road, Mississauga, ON L5S 1J5 Telephone : 905-677-0316  i dealt with them back in the spring,,,,,had all sorts of ss in stock...picked up a refurbished aluminum for my kicker  and fixed my broken one for bout 100.....  ask for louie...       cheers pete
Louie rocks! they do a great job there, unfortunately I've been there more times than I like to admit. He is good and has done tons of props, I'd recommend him to anyone.
